Eastern Cape premier Oscar Mabuyane, who spoke to DispatchLIVE on Friday afternoon, has confirmed that the province now has 17 cases of Covid-19. Komani and Nelson Mandela Metro have the highest number of infections in the province, followed by Buffalo City Metro and Willowvale. In three cases, the locations of those who were infected were still unspecified. Of the 47,965 tests that have been conducted in the country, 1,462 people have tested positive for the virus. Worldwide, confirmed cases passed the 1-million mark on Thursday night as the United states edged toward 250-thousand cases with Italy and Spain each having exceeded 100-thousand confirmed cases. In the public interest, none of our coronavirus news coverage will be behind our paywall. It is available free for all to read. If you would like to support our mission of delivering award-winning, independent local news, please consider taking out a subscription by clicking here.